## 1 Concept Paper

### 1.1 Introduction

This project is a collaborative 3D Unity game developed as part of the PROG2001 Assessment 2. Our team, Team Phoenix, consists of 4 members working together to create a cohesive gaming experience. I am responsible for the Game3 module, which features a fantasy RPG environment with a unique dual-objective completion system. The game requires players to both defeat the boss AND collect 10 magical orbs to achieve victory. This combined objective design creates a more challenging and engaging gameplay experience that encourages exploration and combat.

### 1.2 Team Role - Menu

My role in the team was to design and implement the main menu navigation system. I was responsible for the "Navigation Sprint" during Week 6, where I created a unified menu system that connects all four team members' game scenes. I successfully completed this sprint by:

- Designing a consistent UI style for the main menu
- Implementing scene loading functionality between all game modules
- Creating navigation buttons with proper feedback
- Ensuring the menu works seamlessly across all team members' scenes
- Adding sound effects for menu interactions

The menu features a clean, fantasy-themed design that matches the overall game aesthetic, with clear navigation options to each team member's game and a shared settings menu.

